      Hi! My name is <strong>Milena Alves Ferreira</strong>. I am currently studying 
      Computer Science at the <strong>Universidade Federal de Pelotas (UFPel)</strong>, 
      in Brazil.
    </p>

    <p>
      I built this blog during my <strong>third semester</strong> as part of a job 
      interview challenge. It was my very first contact with <strong>Ruby</strong> and 
      <strong>Ruby on Rails</strong>, and I used the official Rails documentation as my 
      starting point to build everything from scratch.
    </p>

    <p>
      Even though I did not get that particular job, the experience was incredibly 
      valuable. Working with Rails introduced me to a framework I genuinely enjoyed — 
      its conventions, its elegance, and how quickly you can build something functional 
      and real. After the interview, I kept working on the project, adding new features 
      and improving the design, because I wanted to keep learning.
    </p>

    <p>
      This blog is a small but meaningful milestone in my journey as a developer. 
      It represents my first steps into web development with Rails, and I am proud 
      of how far it has come from that initial test.
    </p>

    <p>
      I am always looking to grow, learn new technologies, and take on new challenges. 
      Feel free to explore the articles and reach out!
    </p>
